<br />The AC Adapter has a figure with the + sigh on the left and the - sign on the right, which would mean it's a negative polarity according to this: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:AC_adaptor_polarity.png">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:AC_ad ... larity.png</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />I guess I can buy either of those adapters then, as they're both using minus polarity. Thanks a lot!

		

