	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />AC adapters could be of two types: AC-AC and AC-DC. In this thread all the references to AC or DC are related to second part, i.e. to output, it is the only that matters for NES or clone.
<br />
<br />First adapter you mention in your first post (broken one) is AC-DC (~ means AC, == means DC). You need an AC-DC adapter as replacement. The two on your link to the swedish site are AC-DC, they are suitable.
<br />
<br />Second one you mention in the first post is AC-AC. This one is not suitable.
<br />
<br />For any AC-DC adapter you need to check the polarity.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


